    "rationale": "HIP floor is 5.61 us/node and a HIP graph does NOT beat a native launch loop (1.00x). So the ~20.6 us/op full-path residual is ~73% host-side per-op overhead (15.0 us/op: Python/ctypes marshaling + per-op pointer/bucket setup above the trivial-kernel floor), not HIP dispatch. A micro-bench-tight native C++ verify loop (M16.2: fixed args, baked launch sequence, persistent scratch) collapses the residual toward the 5.28 ms HIP floor at 941 nodes; going below that needs FEWER nodes (M16.3) + lower kernel time (M16.4). A HIP graph buys ~nothing over the native loop (M16.5 de-prioritized). Caveat: M14.dispatch.1's partial MoE dispatcher was parity, so the native loop must match this burst's tightness to realize the floor.",
